arguments.prompt:
You are implementing a Blazor Web App for a logistics company that tracks shipments. The project has already been scaffolded at `/tmp/sv-b9d1b34e761f4b0a91104e95c7aa497a/ShipmentTracker/` using `dotnet new blazor -int Auto -ai -au Individual`.

The project structure:
- `ShipmentTracker/` - server project
- `ShipmentTracker.Client/` - client/WebAssembly project

Key architecture rules for Auto mode with global interactivity:
- All interactive components MUST go in the `.Client` project
- Interactive components cannot access DB directly - must use HTTP APIs
- Define service interfaces in `.Client`, implement with HttpClient there, implement with direct DB access on server
- Both Program.cs files must register matching services
- No `@rendermode` needed on pages (global mode)

## What to implement

### 1. Shared Model - Create in Client project (since both projects reference it)

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Models/Shipment.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

public class Shipment
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string TrackingNumber { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Origin { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Destination { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public ShipmentStatus Status { get; set; }
    public DateTime ShippedDate { get; set; }
    public DateTime EstimatedDelivery { get; set; }
    public string CustomerEmail { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Description { get; set; } = string.Empty;
}

public enum ShipmentStatus
{
    Pending,
    PickedUp,
    InTransit,
    OutForDelivery,
    Delivered,
    Delayed
}
```

### 2. Service Interface - in Client project

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/IShipmentService.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

public interface IShipmentService
{
    Task<List<Shipment>> GetAllShipmentsAsync();
    Task<Shipment?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber);
    Task UpdateShipmentStatusAsync(int id, ShipmentStatus status);
}
```

### 3. Client-side implementation using HttpClient

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/ShipmentHttpService.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

using System.Net.Http.Json;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

public class ShipmentHttpService : IShipmentService
{
    private readonly HttpClient _http;

    public ShipmentHttpService(HttpClient http)
    {
        _http = http;
    }

    public async Task<List<Shipment>> GetAllShipmentsAsync()
    {
        return await _http.GetFromJsonAsync<List<Shipment>>("api/shipments") ?? [];
    }

    public async Task<Shipment?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber)
    {
        return await _http.GetFromJsonAsync<Shipment?>($"api/shipments/track/{trackingNumber}");
    }

    public async Task UpdateShipmentStatusAsync(int id, ShipmentStatus status)
    {
        await _http.PutAsJsonAsync($"api/shipments/{id}/status", status);
    }
}
```

### 4. Register HttpClient and services in Client Program.cs

Edit `ShipmentTracker.Client/Program.cs` to:
```csharp
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.WebAssembly.Hosting;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

var builder = WebAssemblyHostBuilder.CreateDefault(args);

builder.Services.AddAuthorizationCore();
builder.Services.AddCascadingAuthenticationState();
builder.Services.AddAuthenticationStateDeserialization();

builder.Services.AddHttpClient("ServerAPI", client =>
    client.BaseAddress = new Uri(builder.HostEnvironment.BaseAddress));
builder.Services.AddScoped(sp =>
    sp.GetRequiredService<IHttpClientFactory>().CreateClient("ServerAPI"));
builder.Services.AddScoped<IShipmentService, ShipmentHttpService>();

await builder.Build().RunAsync();
```

### 5. Server-side service implementation

Create `ShipmentTracker/Services/ShipmentServerService.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Services;

using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;
using ShipmentTracker.Data;
using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore;

public class ShipmentServerService : IShipmentService
{
    private readonly ApplicationDbContext _db;

    public ShipmentServerService(ApplicationDbContext db)
    {
        _db = db;
    }

    public async Task<List<Shipment>> GetAllShipmentsAsync()
    {
        return await _db.Shipments.OrderByDescending(s => s.ShippedDate).ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Shipment?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber)
    {
        return await _db.Shipments.FirstOrDefaultAsync(s => s.TrackingNumber == trackingNumber);
    }

    public async Task UpdateShipmentStatusAsync(int id, ShipmentStatus status)
    {
        var shipment = await _db.Shipments.FindAsync(id);
        if (shipment is not null)
        {
            shipment.Status = status;
            await _db.SaveChangesAsync();
        }
    }
}
```

### 6. Add Shipment DbSet to ApplicationDbContext

Look at the existing `ShipmentTracker/Data/ApplicationDbContext.cs` and add:
```csharp
public DbSet<Shipment> Shipments => Set<Shipment>();
```
Make sure to add `using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;` at the top.

### 7. API Endpoints

Create `ShipmentTracker/Endpoints/ShipmentEndpoints.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Endpoints;

using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;
using ShipmentTracker.Data;
using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore;

public static class ShipmentEndpoints
{
    public static void MapShipmentEndpoints(this WebApplication app)
    {
        var group = app.MapGroup("api/shipments").RequireAuthorization();

        group.MapGet("", async (ApplicationDbContext db) =>
            await db.Shipments.OrderByDescending(s => s.ShippedDate).ToListAsync());

        group.MapGet("track/{trackingNumber}", async (string trackingNumber, ApplicationDbContext db) =>
        {
            var shipment = await db.Shipments.FirstOrDefaultAsync(s => s.TrackingNumber == trackingNumber);
            return shipment is not null ? Results.Ok(shipment) : Results.NotFound();
        }).AllowAnonymous();

        group.MapPut("{id}/status", async (int id, ShipmentStatus status, ApplicationDbContext db) =>
        {
            var shipment = await db.Shipments.FindAsync(id);
            if (shipment is null) return Results.NotFound();
            shipment.Status = status;
            await db.SaveChangesAsync();
            return Results.NoContent();
        });
    }
}
```

Note: The track endpoint is AllowAnonymous so customers can track without logging in. The list and update endpoints require auth (dispatchers).

### 8. Register server services and map endpoints in server Program.cs

Add to `ShipmentTracker/Program.cs`:
- Add `using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;` and `using ShipmentTracker.Services;` and `using ShipmentTracker.Endpoints;`
- After the existing service registrations, add: `builder.Services.AddScoped<IShipmentService, ShipmentServerService>();`
- After `app.MapAdditionalIdentityEndpoints();`, add: `app.MapShipmentEndpoints();`

### 9. Seed data

Create `ShipmentTracker/Data/SeedData.cs`:
